rComments: Classes are pretty dull and mostly based on the textbook. She reads off of her slides verbatim but you still have to go to class to get attendance marks ...zzzZZZzzzz, take it during the year with Gillian

Unapproachable attitude from the get go. She's dissmissive, condescending, and not very sympathetic. Her slides are a direct transcript of the textbook and she basically reads off the slides. Wish I would have known I never needed to attend class! Class is easy and would be more enjoyable if she was more firendly and sensitive to student needs!

Her teaching is nothing special, but it gets the job done. She seems mean, but she's actually quite nice and helpful. Tests are quite easy (mix of SA/fill in blanks/MC). Overall,her version of the course is probably easier compared to Einstein's (which i hear has a lot more writing involved)but Einstein's is probably more interesting.

She is god awful. I'm feel bad for anyone who takes her class in the future, and embarrassed that the department let her teach. Hopefully her research is awesome b/c she'll never make it as a real prof. Take this class with Prof. Einstein, the quality difference is night and day!
